OL,6,FFormer Manchester United midfielder
OL,7,FStiles, who was part of the England
OL,8,Fteam which won the World Cup on home
OL,9,Fsoil in 1966, died in 2020 having
OL,10,Flived with the disease for several
OL,11,Fyears.
OL,13,FStiles had been diagnosed with
OL,14,Fprostate cancer in 2013, but a
OL,15,Fpostmortem examination of his brain
OL,16,Ffound he had chronic traumatic
OL,17,Fencephalopathy (CTE), a progressive
OL,18,Fneurodegenerative disease associated
OL,19,Fwith repeated head traumas.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/13
